The article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on April 10, 2020. The memorandum authorizes the Secretary of Veterans Affairs to exercise authority under Public Law 85-804, as amended, in response to the ongoing outbreak of COVID-19. This authority allows the Department of Veterans Affairs to enter into contracts in support of efforts to combat the virus. The memorandum states that these actions are necessary for the national defense and will terminate on September 30, 2020. The memorandum also clarifies that it does not affect other existing authorities or functions and should be implemented in accordance with applicable law and available funding.